                type="document" xml:id="d400">
                <head>No. 400<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On April 16, President <persName corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Eisenhower</persName>
                    delivered the address about which he had consulted with <persName
                        corresp="#p_CHURCHILLWS1">Churchill</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_MAYERR1">Mayer</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_ADENAUERK1"
                        >Adenauer</persName>. For the text of the address, see <hi rend="italic"
                        >Public Papers of the Presidents of the United States: <persName
                            corresp="#p_EISENHOWER1">Dwight D. Eisenhower</persName>, 1953</hi>,
                    pages 179–188, or Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, April 27,
                    1953, pages 599–603. Reaction to the speech as reported from the various United
                    States posts abroad is in file 611.00.</p>
            </div>
